Open "Server Manager" and click on "Add roles and features."
Select "Active Directory Certificate Services" and follow the wizard to install the role.
After installing the role, open "Certification Authority" from the Tools menu.
Follow the wizard to configure the AD CS role, including selecting the CA type and setting up the CA.
After configuring Active Directory Certificate Services, you'll have a centralized PKI infrastructure to issue and manage digital certificates for secure communication and authentication within your network.
